parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the loss of anti-lock braking capability, leading to reduced vehicle safety and increased risk of accidents, especially when towing heavy trailers.
symptoms: the "Service ABS" or "Service Electronic Braking System" message is displayed
the traction control system is disabled
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle's brakes may not function properly
and the warning chimes or bell sounds continuously.

and the warning chimes or bell sounds continuously.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the HCU can cause the Anti-lock Brake System (ABS) and traction control to malfunction, leading to loss of braking power, making it difficult to control the vehicle, especially when towing or driving in hazardous conditions.
symptoms: Intermittent flashing of ABS and traction control lights
